	url = {https://www.davidrumsey.com/luna/servlet/detail/RUMSEY~8~1~354715~90121670:Composite-text--The-commercial-and-},
	abstract = {This image displays a composite view of William Playfair's "The Commercial and Political Atlas," specifically the third edition published in 1801 by T. Burton. The work is significant for its pioneering use of graphical representations to depict data, a novel approach at the time. This atlas is a thematic collection focused on visualizing the commerce, revenues, expenditure, and debts of England during the eighteenth century.{\textless}br{\textgreater}{\textless}br{\textgreater}Composition and Medium:{\textless}br{\textgreater}
